menuconfig BRICKPI
	tristate "Dexter Industries BrickPi support"
	select SERIAL_DEV_BUS
	help
	  Say Y here if you want to use Dexter Industries BrickPi. This does not
	  include the LEDs or I2C on input port 5, both of which need to be
	  configured manually.

	  To compile this driver as a module, choose M here: the
	  module will be called brickpi.

menuconfig BRICKPI_BATTERY
    tristate "Dexter Industries BrickPi+ battery support"
    help
      Say Y here if you want to use Dexter Industries BrickPi+. This provides
      a power_supply class driver to monitor the battery voltage.

      To compile this driver as a module, choose M here: the
      module will be called brickpi-battery.
